<p>Given following XML:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;test id="s1-t2" name="Lorem ipsum"&gt;     ...     &lt;tags&gt;         &lt;tag&gt;foo&lt;/tag&gt;         &lt;tag&gt;bar&lt;/tag&gt;     &lt;/tags&gt;     ... &lt;/test&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I'd like to append the node value of each tag element in name attribute of test element. So the resulting XML should be like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;test id="s1-t2" name="Lorem ipsum [foo][bar]"&gt;     ...     &lt;tags&gt;         &lt;tag&gt;foo&lt;/tag&gt;         &lt;tag&gt;bar&lt;/tag&gt;     &lt;/tags&gt;     ... &lt;/test&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The tags element (and its content) can remain in place, but it is not necessary.</p>  <p>So far I've tried something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xsl:template match="test"&gt;     &lt;test&gt;         &lt;xsl:copy-of select="@*"/&gt;         &lt;xsl:attribute name="name"&gt;             &lt;xsl:value-of select="tags/tag"/&gt;         &lt;/xsl:attribute&gt;         &lt;xsl:apply-templates select="node()"/&gt;     &lt;/test&gt; &lt;/xsl:template&gt; </code></pre>  <p>but that does not work. And even if it would work, it would replace the name attribute and only with one tag. It's been too long since I last wrote any XSLT.</p>